com.hcl.domino.naming

Interface UserDirectoryQuery

  • All Superinterfaces:
    SearchQuery

    public interface UserDirectoryQuery
extends SearchQuery
    Represents a query into the names directory system of the local runtime or a remote server.
    Since:
    1.0.2
    Author:
    Jesse Gallagher

    • Method Summary

      • namespaces

        UserDirectoryQuery namespaces(Collection<String> namespaces)
        Instructs the query to search the provided namespaces, which in practice correspond to Domino view names. The default for this setting is to search "$Users".

        If specified, this must be non-null and non-empty.

        Parameters:
        namespaces - a Collection of namespace names to search
        Returns:
        this query builder

      • namespaces

        default UserDirectoryQuery namespaces(String... namespaces)
        Instructs the query to search the provided namespaces, which in practice correspond to Domino view names. The default for this setting is to search "$Users".
        Parameters:
        namespaces - the namespaces names to search
        Returns:
        this query builder
        Since:
        1.0.17

      • names

        UserDirectoryQuery names(Collection<String> names)
        Specifies the names to look up. If unspecified, the query will return all entries in the specified namespaces.
        Parameters:
        names - a Collection of string names to look up
        Returns:
        this query builder

      • items

        UserDirectoryQuery items(Collection<String> items)
        Specifies the items to extract from found directory entries.

        This must be specified before a call to stream()

        Parameters:
        items - a Collection of item names
        Returns:
        this query builder

      • stream

        Stream<List<Map<String,List<Object>>>> stream()
        Executes and retrieves a stream of results from the query.

        The result stream will contain one entry per queried name per queried namespace. Each of those entries will contain a list of matches for the name+namespace pair.

        Returns:
        a Stream of List<Map<String, Object>> lookup results for this query
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if items(Collection) has not been specified or if either it or namespaces(Collection) is set to null or empty
